    'body' => '	I think alot of you are being a little hard on this show.  Has
anyone seen anything with on TV or in movies (besides 2001 and 2010) with
realistic space flight?  I don\'t think you can say that B5\'s space combat
is any more realistic.  Anything being done at visual range is really kind
of silly, but you\'ve got to do it or it gets boring to look at (though I
think with really good writers you could swing it, the public just
wouldn\'t _get_ realistic space flight and combat).  
	In terms of B5 being a much better show, this is true, but only in
recent years (IMO).  The first season or two (BB, or "Before Boxlietner")
were quite iffy to say the least.  This sort of thing has been true of
every SF show on the tube.  I think compared to ST:TNE and its brethren
(AKA S&S or "Soap Operas & Space Anomalies"), this is a much better show. 
They need to work out some kinks, and concentrate on space combat more. 
The idea of the pilots being ground forces could be excused on several
grounds which others have noted, and I don\'t really care about "military 
structure" accuracy anyway. Lots can change in 60 years or so.
	 I actually think their treatment of "Vat Soldiers" is really well
done.  The idea that they would have stunted social skills meshes well
with the total lack of socialization they would recieve while being
"grown".  I also like the idea that they are not too "super-human".  It
really isn\'t that easy to mess with the human genome, and it\'s not
necessary if you can just produce oodles of average-joe soldiers (with 
20/20 vision and other basics taken care of by selection).  There\'s also 
the problem (politically) of creating a "superior race".  The fact that 
some of them resent being created just to die for normal humans makes 
sense to me too (_I\'d_ be pissed off!).
	That having been said, the show does get a little too 
touchy-feely at times, but hopefully they will remedy this in the coming 
season.

Charles.

