    'body' => '
>2) On Sunday\'s, show a "Vitro", who even spent most of his life on the
>lamb 
(uh, that\'s lam, or are you saying something about his sex preferences :-)
>didn\'t know what Christmas was.  Did he really live on Earth, let
>alone the US--even 100 years from now?
I thought that was more than a little lame, too.

>3) Why is there a Saratoga?  It appears that there was no other space
>capable .military--precontact.  Why build it?
That\'s easy.  There are still separate governments.  That\'s the USS Saratoga 
on loan to the UN; the 58th are US marines, not UN troops. Traveller:2300
had a similar premise for a UN conglomeration of vessels belonging to 
different nations ganging up on a common invader (Kafers).

>4) The "58th" has about a dozen LTs and a Major.  Where are the Captains,
>let alone the enlisted men?
Actually, that\'s a Lt Col - and a bunch of LTs.  There should be a Captain
or two
even in a brandy new squadron.  Not to mention that the fighter maintenance folk
should be USMC enlisted attached to the 58th. (not to mention the idiocy of 
sending expensively trained fighter pilots on grunt missions...)

>5) What about grav plates?  When they lose their power they still have gravity.
Now, now.  0G effects are expensive :-) You don\'t see many on B5 either.

>9) Why do fighters bank in vacuum?
Most viewers would understand when fighters pivot, fire main engine, and then
start following a separate vector (curving path while the engine fires).
Star Wars 
